low our religion and my brother up to the end was repeatedly making attempts to get for us the permission to hold church services and for that reason he disappeared one day. More we were unable to learn about him. Later it was said he was accused of the possession of a radio because his radio was taken away right with his arrest."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3607.485","u": "Was it not permitted to have a radio?"},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3609.938","u": "It was not prohibited officially but from the Mennonites all the radio sets were taken away. And from my brother they took it at the moment of his arrest. And so he died after two years imprisonment. But earlier, 1935, we still could write letters to each other, to the prison. As I told you before, among us Mennonites it was not permitted to marry with people of another nationality or religion, but my sister, my younger sister married a Tartar. He was an engineer and was assigned to work between Leningrad and Onega Lake. They were building there the functions in the systems of canals."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3663.646","u": "Near Leningrad?"},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3664.490","u": "Near Leningrad. There he was working."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3666.983","u": "And what lake did you mention?"},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3668.807","u": "Onega Lake."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3670.023","u": "Oh. Onega Lake."},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3671.420","u": "Onegskoe Ozero."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3673.410","u": "Oh, yes. Onegskoe Ozero. How well you pronounce it in Russian.[They both laugh heartily]"},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3677.983","u": "Yes. And since then I know nothing about my sister, nothing about her whereabouts. Then there was my other sister. She too was away in Bartke[?]"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3691.481","u": "Where is that?"},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3699.538","u": "In Poland. And afterwards we were unable to find her, but through America we have now received from her a postcard. She has written a postcard from Siberia to America and our relatives in America have copied for us the postcard and sent it to us and that is how we know the address of my sister."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3731.125","u": "Well, she was not deported to Siberia?"},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3734.617","u": "We don&#39;t know."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3735.592","u": "Life in Siberia as such is not so bad."},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3738.406","u": "Oh, no. It is not bad."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3740.999","u": "Well, that is fortunate. Oh, yes. She was in Poland and so many from Poland were evacuated to Siberia. That is very possible. Many who survived were evacuated to Siberia."},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3750.154","u": "And so we don&#39;t know why she has been sent there."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3754.953","u": "Now tell me how do you live here in the lager? How many Mennonites are here in the lager and how do you live here?"},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3761.963","u": "We are here about six hundred Mennonites."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3772.451","u": "About how many men, women and children?"},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3775.627","u": "[Hesitantly]We have here about 300 to 350 children."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3787.204","u": "Is that so?"},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3787.901","u": "The rest are women and men. Among them mostly women. The number of men is relatively small."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3799.303","u": "Tell me approximately how many women are here with their husbands?"},    {"who": "Anna Braun", "start": "3804.112","u": "We have here very few women with their husbands. We have here either women without their husbands or men without their wives."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3812.801","u": "D